FBIS4-61011 "drsov085_t_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-085 Daily Report 2 May 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia President Postpones Rome Visit, Wishes Pope Rapid Recovery President Postpones Rome Visit, Wishes Pope Rapid Recovery WS0205115194 Tallinn ETA in English 0909 GMT 2 May 94 WS0205115194 Tallinn ETA English BFN ["News Release"] [Text] Tallinn, 1 May -- Estonian President Lennart Meri has decided to postpone his friendship visit to Italy and Rome earlier scheduled for 3-6 May until September, the President's press office said. Pope John Paul II on Thursday [28 April] tripped on his robe and fractured his hip. Meri has sent the Pope a letter wishing him rapid recovery.
